is variation is indicative of\nthe deformation process that occurred in the past, and the western bulge is\nmore relaxed structurally than the other region. Our analysis also shows that\nthis deformation process might occur at a spin period between ~3.5 h and ~3.0\nh, providing the cohesive strength ranging between ~4 Pa and ~10 Pa.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 6 Apr 2019 15:57:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-09"}
